The House of Representatives passed a $2 trillion emergency relief package Friday that contained several pro-life protections.
The relief package, the CARES Act, passed the House on Friday afternoon after passing the Senate 96-0 on Wednesday night.
“Republicans won critical pro-life protections in this relief package, despite a last-minute attempt by Democrats to make Planned Parenthood eligible for disaster-relief funding,” Sen. Tom Cotton told the Daily Caller News Foundation on Friday.
No part of it should be abused to end lives.” (RELATED: Louisiana Department Of Health Refuses To Specify If Abortions Are Banned)I just signed the CARES Act, the single biggest economic relief package in American History – twice as large as any relief bill ever enacted.
At $2.2 Trillion Dollars, this bill will deliver urgently-needed relief for our nation’s families, workers, and businesses.